cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on attacking neural text detectors, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential danger of misinformation spread by language models, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The attacks proposed in the paper involve machine learning techniques, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques for generating homoglyphs, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
